---
import { aboutMeta } from '../data/portfolio';
---

<section id="about" class="statement wrap" aria-labelledby="about-h">
  <p class="eyebrow">About Pratik</p>
  <h2 id="about-h">A product-minded mobile engineer focused on apps that <em>survive production.</em></h2>
  <div class="about-cols">
    <div class="lead">
      <p>I care about the whole life of an app — the architecture underneath it, the tests around it, and the person tapping on it. Since 2021 I've shipped Flutter apps across <b>HealthTech, e-commerce, agri-tech and restaurant tech</b>: payment systems that talk to physical card readers, offline-first tools for farmers, POS platforms that keep restaurants running through the dinner rush, and member-facing care flows in mental-health products.</p>
      <p>I like the parts most people skip — foundations, tooling, code generation — and I use <b>AI agentic tools</b> (Cursor, Claude Code, custom PR-review agents) the same way: wrapped in tests, guardrails, and a human who reads every diff. I'd rather spend a day automating boilerplate than a week typing it.</p>
    </div>
    <dl class="about-meta">
      {aboutMeta.map((row) => (
        <div class="meta-row">
          <dt>{row.label}</dt>
          <dd set:html={row.valueHtml} />
        </div>
      ))}
    </dl>
  </div>
</section>
